                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#58v"/>
                    <desc>
                    Colophon: “This book of Abu Shaker, I Kinä Selassie [baptismal name for Nəburä ‘Ǝdə Dəmeṭəros Gäbrä Maryam) commissioned by my own money for the memory of goodness so that the history of the Ethiopian church will not be forgotten and the memory of the Father from Adam up to [the present]. In 1956 EC, in the thirty-second year of the reign of Ḫaylä Selassie I, king of kings of Ethiopia, I Kinä Selassie, with my wife Walatta Haymanot. O, my brothers who are reading this book, do not forget one “Our Father” [for me]. O, my children, I beseech all of you, do not forget the worship of your God: Gedewon, Gədäy (baptismal name, Śəga Maryam), Yoftahe, Ǝnbaqom, Somson, Śara.”
                    </desc>
